cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a novel network model based on Graph Neural Networks (GNN) for network modeling and optimization in Software-Defined Networks (SDN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) which deals with neural networks and their applications. The paper also discusses the ability of GNNs to learn and model graph-structured information, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes a model that can produce accurate predictions of Key Performance Indicators (KPI) such as delay, jitter or loss, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use-cases where the KPI predictions of the GNN model are leveraged to achieve efficient routing optimization and network planning, which makes cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) other likely categories.
